result.execSummary:
The defendant Allen K Umentum was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Penalty - Retail Theft (>$500 - $5000)], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Bond from 15CF377 shall be applied first towards the restitution and then towards all remaining fees and costs. If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall have no contact with any Washington County Walmart.

Defendant shall have no contact with Sandra Weiss.

Defendant shall not consume any controlled substance.

Defendant shall not possess any controlled substance without a valid prescription.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent.

Defendant shall, within three (3) days, contact the Washington County Jail for purposes of supplying a biological specimen for DNA analysis.

Defendant shall take all medications as prescribed.
